PROBLEM STATEMENT
Project: MindfulWork App — Smart Stress Relief Pod System

Background:
Workplace burnout is at an all-time high. Over 60% of employees experience daily stressors that negatively affect their performance, motivation, and mental health. 
Traditional stress management tools such as general wellness workshops, scheduled breaks, and broad mental health programs fail to provide instant, personalized relief tailored to individual needs. 
Employees across all job roles and age groups struggle to find quick, private, and effective ways to manage stress during the workday without disrupting their workflow.

User Research Insights:
Through research, surveys, and empathy mapping across 10 employee personas, the following key pain points were identified:

- Employees feel they have no time or private space to decompress during work hours
- Stress triggers vary significantly across job roles, ages, and personality types
- Existing wellness programs are too generic and not personalized to individual needs
- Employees are reluctant to show stress openly in a professional environment
- There is no easy, on-demand system that combines sensory relaxation with AI-driven personalization


Problem Statement:
How might we design a smart, AI-powered app that offers instant, personalized, and private stress relief sessions for employees 
— adjusting music, lighting, and aroma to individual stress levels 
— so that employees can reduce stress quickly and return to peak productivity without disrupting their workflow?

Target Users:
Employees across all departments and job roles, aged 24—45, experiencing daily workplace stress

Design Goal:
To create an app prototype that manages the Smart Stress Relief Pod experience by gathering stress inputs, personalizing pod sessions using MoodSync AI, and providing tools for breathing exercises, session scheduling, and reflective journaling
